If the interviewer asks "How does it make the application loosely coupled?", continue with:
The class depends on an interface rather than a concrete class. For example, if Car depends on IEngine, I can inject PetrolEngine, DieselEngine, or ElectricEngine without changing the Car class. 
I only change the implementation that's registered with the DI container.

What is Transient ?
A Transient service creates a new object every time it is resolved by the DI container. It does not create a new object every time a method is called on an existing instance.
Transient is a service lifetime in ASP.NET Core Dependency Injection. When a service is registered as Transient, the DI container creates a new instance every time the service is resolved.
It is generally used for lightweight, stateless services.
Resolving a service means the DI container creates or returns an instance of the requested service.

what is a lifetime service?
A service lifetime defines how long an object created by the Dependency Injection (DI) container should exist before it is discarded or recreated.

what is scope service?
We use Scoped services when the same service instance should be shared throughout a single HTTP request but not across different requests.
It is commonly used for DbContext, repositories, and business services because all operations within one request use the same object, ensuring consistency and avoiding unnecessary object creation. 
A new instance is created for each new HTTP request

DbContext represents a unit of work for a single request and is not thread-safe. Registering it as Scoped ensures each HTTP request gets its own DbContext instance, preventing data conflicts and concurrency 
issues while keeping all database operations within that request consistent.

What is Singleton?

Definition:

Singleton is a service lifetime where the DI container creates only one instance of the service and shares that same instance across all HTTP requests for the entire lifetime of the application.
