what is application lifetime?
When you deploy your ASP.NET Core application to IIS, Azure, Docker, or another server:
The application starts running.
It begins accepting HTTP requests.
This is the start of the application lifetime.
It continues running until:
You stop the application.
You restart the server.
You redeploy a new version.
The application crashes or is recycled by the server.

Then the application lifetime ends.






